                            <comment id="13559182" author="daijy" created="Mon, 21 Jan 2013 22:44:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Seems it has been optimized by rule FilterAboveForeach. The test case testForeachFilter is confusing, we should put the following remark: PushDownForEachFlatten does not apply here because Pig decide to leave it to rule FilterAboveForeach.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13559211" author="njw45" created="Mon, 21 Jan 2013 23:34:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ah yes - that makes sense. I&apos;ve updated the patch to just include the comments you mention and an extra unit test...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13560244" author="jcoveney" created="Wed, 23 Jan 2013 00:42:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Nick,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The new patch does not include a lot of changes from the old one. Can you upload a definitive patch?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13560250" author="daijy" created="Wed, 23 Jan 2013 00:47:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Nick added a test case and some comments, but remove the code fix in the new patch I believe.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13560304" author="njw45" created="Wed, 23 Jan 2013 01:56:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Indeed - Daniel pointed out the code changes weren&apos;t necessary as this optimisation is done by a different Rule. I&apos;ve left a patch with comments to that effect so it&apos;s clearer for the next person reading the code &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.gif&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13561130" author="daijy" created="Wed, 23 Jan 2013 21:53:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch committed to trunk. Thanks Nick!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
